<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,929,1134]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Comparison of photograph of the holotype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1881" box="[663,880,930,953]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Carterica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaea">
<emphasis box="[663,880,930,953]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Carterica pygmaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation box="[938,1083,929,954]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref18920" refString="Bezark, L. G. (2017) A photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the New World. Available from: https: // apps 2. cdfa. ca. gov / publicApps / plant / bycidDB / wsearch. asp? w = n (accessed 30 August 2017)" type="journal article">Bezark 2017</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[1094,1219,930,954]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref19519" refString="Maes, J. - M., Berghe, E., Dauber, D., Audureau, A., Nearns, E., Skillman, F., Heffern, D. &amp; Monne, M. A. (2010) Catalogo ilustrado de los Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) de Nicaragua. Parte IV-Lamiinae-Disteniinae. Revista Nicaraguense de Entomologia, 70 (Suplemento 1 - 4), 1 - 873." type="journal article">Maes 2010</bibRefCitation>
) with the specimen from Nicaragua (Mataglapa, Selva Negra Mountain Resort) in 
<bibRefCitation box="[856,1001,966,990]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref19519" refString="Maes, J. - M., Berghe, E., Dauber, D., Audureau, A., Nearns, E., Skillman, F., Heffern, D. &amp; Monne, M. A. (2010) Catalogo ilustrado de los Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) de Nicaragua. Parte IV-Lamiinae-Disteniinae. Revista Nicaraguense de Entomologia, 70 (Suplemento 1 - 4), 1 - 873." type="journal article">Maes (2010)</bibRefCitation>
, affirms that they are different species. The 
<bibRefCitation box="[201,344,1002,1026]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref19519" refString="Maes, J. - M., Berghe, E., Dauber, D., Audureau, A., Nearns, E., Skillman, F., Heffern, D. &amp; Monne, M. A. (2010) Catalogo ilustrado de los Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) de Nicaragua. Parte IV-Lamiinae-Disteniinae. Revista Nicaraguense de Entomologia, 70 (Suplemento 1 - 4), 1 - 873." type="journal article">Maes (2010)</bibRefCitation>
specimen is much more slender and has different proportions between head, prothorax and elytra so it is very likely an undescribed species. Nearly all specimens examined by us through photographs or the single specimen deposited at MZSP, show slender specimens, in some cases, with distinctly longer legs. However, until additional specimens are available it is not possible to know if more than one species is represented among them.
</paragraph>
